news.title: China: Longfor Group prices $219 million bonds at a coupon rate of 3.3%
news.para: Longfor's three-year notes, priced at the lower end of an indicative range of 3% to 4.3%, were oversubscribed by 2.86 times, the company and market sources said. The offering was guaranteed by state-owned China Bond Insurance Co Ltd.

news.title: YES Bank leases 44,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Goregaon suburb
news.para: As per the lease agreement, the bank will be paying lease rental of Rs 53.19 lakh per month, taking its annual rental pay out to nearly Rs 6.40 crore. The bank has also paid security deposits worth nearly Rs 3.07 crore for the transaction.

news.title: UP RERA increases validity of registration of real estate agents to 10 years
news.para: Registered real estate agents in UP have been issued a "registration certificate" in Form-H prescribed in the UP RERA Rules. In this, the validity period of registration is five years. In Rule-10(3) of the UP Land Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2016, the period of registration of a real estate agent has been fixed at 10 years.

news.title: HDFC Property Ventures, HDFC Venture Cap to be merged with HDFC Capital Advisors
news.para: The proposed scheme of amalgamation envisages merger of both the transferor companies with and into transferee company HDFC Capital Advisors and the dissolution of the transferor companies without being wound up.

news.title: Elan Group concludes 40 acre land deal with Indiabulls Real Estate in Gurugram
news.para: ​In January, the company had announced purchase of around 40 acres of land in Gurugram from Indiabulls Real Estate Ltd (IBREL) for Rs 580 crore for the development of housing and commercial projects.

news.title: JMRC awaits financial approval from government for Jaipur Metro phase-1D project
news.para: Under the project, the JMRC has proposed to construct approximately 2km elevated stretch connecting Mansarovar and 200-feet bypass at Ajmer Road.

news.title: New Delhi municipal council move may allow more time for paying property tax
news.para: There are 13,485 private and 1,494 government offices under NDMC. The civic body usually finalises its budget for the next financial year by January 15, but takes a decision on property tax rates and rebates in the council meeting that takes place a month later.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA records 7,631 unauthorized structures, registers FIR against 94
news.para: While FIR has been registered against 94 structures, 263 structures have been demolished to date. These structures are in Maval, Mulshi, Haveli and Khed talukas of the PMRDA region.

news.title: Mumbai: Property tax hike deferred yet again in year of BMC poll
news.para: Shinde said according to the BMC Act, property tax is revised every five years, but revision was delayed in 2020 due to the pandemic, and it was due for revision this year.

news.title: Reduce delay in property registration at sub-registrar's office: Realtors
news.para: GAR has also welcomed transfers and reshuffle among the civil-cum-sub registrars and has thanked chief minister Pramod Sawant for his intervention which resulted in reshuffle.

news.title: Adani Group launches Rs 31,000 crore open offer for ACC, Ambuja Cements
news.para: In two separate regulatory filings, Ambuja Cements and ACC have submitted their letter of offers for the open offer, launched by the Adani family group's Mauritius-based firm Endeavour Trade and Investment.

news.title: Mumbai: CAG denounces poor performance of BMC in property tax collection
news.para: Among ULBs, average collection efficiency in municipal corporations was 47%, way better than BMC, suggested the report.

news.title: Government to offer Rs 70,000 loan per beneficiary to help complete PMAY-Gramin houses
news.para: The government has set an ambitious target of completing 2,71,92,795 pucca houses under PMAY (Gramin) by March 2024. According to the rural development ministry statistics, 1,96,62,963 houses have been completed.

news.title: Hidco starts e-auction of 5.6 acre land in Alipore
news.para: Officials said the auction's starting bid price was Rs 236.7 crore, standing at Rs 42.3 crore per acre. A state secretariat official said five agencies participated in the bidding.

news.title: Mumbai: Special CBI court cancels builder Satyen Tandon's bail
news.para: The court had then observed that though there was prima facie evidence against him, since he had deposited Rs 4 crore, it was a mitigating factor for granting bail.
